{"TopicId":181547,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.8.1-1] [PLEASE FORK ME] Kopernicus \u0026amp; KittopiaTech","CreatedByName":"Thomas P.","CreatedById":113164,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-26T17:52:56Z","PageNum":83,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"DMagic","CreatedById":57416,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-16T01:59:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113164-thomas-p/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022113164\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113164-thomas-p/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Thomas P.\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Does Kopernicus support using localized biome names? I don\u0027t see anything about setting the displayName field in the BiomeLoader class.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-16T05:56:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223093144\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140580\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497578399\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257416\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DMagic\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, DMagic said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113164-thomas-p/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022113164\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113164-thomas-p/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Thomas P.\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Does Kopernicus support using localized biome names? I don\u0027t see anything about setting the displayName field in the BiomeLoader class.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI assume from reading this that now biomes also have \u0022displayName\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf that\u0027s the case I doubt you can change that with kopernicus, I can take a look and make a PR when I have some time\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Errol","CreatedById":118622,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-16T06:01:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBeen out of the loop for a few days. I just upgraded from 1.3.0-2 to 1.3.0-4 and encountered a weird bug. Game loads to menu fine, but when I try to load a save I get stuck partially on loading screen. What I mean is that mod dialogues show up, like the RT settings dialogue on new saves and the KCT build window, but the screen stays black with the planets loading icon in the lower right corner. Also; it is missing the word LOADING when this happens. Reverting to 1.3.0-2 fixes it. I tried 1.3.0-3 as well and got the exact same bug.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-16T06:07:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223093293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140580\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497592873\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022118622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Errol\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Errol said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBeen out of the loop for a few days. I just upgraded from 1.3.0-2 to 1.3.0-4 and encountered a weird bug. Game loads to menu fine, but when I try to load a save I get stuck partially on loading screen. What I mean is that mod dialogues show up, like the RT settings dialogue on new saves and the KCT build window, but the screen stays black with the planets loading icon in the lower right corner. Also; it is missing the word LOADING when this happens. Reverting to 1.3.0-2 fixes it. I tried 1.3.0-3 as well and got the exact same bug.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you are using any of my mods, don\u0027t.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI haven\u0027t had time to update them to the latest Kopernicus yet\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you are not, send us some logs and we\u0027ll take a look (click the nyan cat in my sig for the list of files)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Errol","CreatedById":118622,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-16T06:23:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003EDoes Urlum tilt count?\u003C/s\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nEdit: Oh yeah, wait, I\u0027m using sigma binary....never mind, I\u0027ll see myself out..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-16T06:24:11Z\u0022 title=\u002206/16/2017 06:24  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 16, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Errol\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DMagic","CreatedById":57416,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-16T15:37:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223093288\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140580\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497592603\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022113260\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sigma88\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, Sigma88 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI assume from reading this that now biomes also have \u0022displayName\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf that\u0027s the case I doubt you can change that with kopernicus, I can take a look and make a PR when I have some time\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, specifically, the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://kerbalspaceprogram.com/api/class_c_b_attribute_map_s_o_1_1_map_attribute.html#ac0c5207b4a1257f963f805274a094a47\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ECBAttributeMapSO.MapAttribute\u003C/a\u003E has a displayName (and localizationTag, which I\u0027m not sure what the purpose of is), which, at least in some cases appears to be the unformatted localization string (#autoLOC...) so that you have to call Localizer.Format on it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nScience results and some other things need to be able to read both the standard and the display name for the biome. ScienceUtil.GetExperimentBiomeLocalized and GetBiomeDisplayName are used quite a bit and both return only the displayName.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe last section of the modders notes goes over it a little, with further complications if anyone is trying to set \u0022mini-biomes\u0022 - \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E biomes:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/157804-modders-notes-for-13/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-16T15:58:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57416-dmagic/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257416\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57416-dmagic/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@DMagic\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0the purpose is most likely to allow for biome names to be translated from english (eg grasslands) to other languages, without the need of changing all the science defs keys (eg kerbinsrflandedgrasslands)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DMagic","CreatedById":57416,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-16T16:08:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113260-sigma88/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022113260\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113260-sigma88/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Sigma88\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Yes, all components of the science id\u0027s (experiment title, body name, situation, and biome) remain in english. The display names are just used for the title that actually shows up in the experiment results window. Biome names are in lots of places, though. Stock modules might have better handling of the situation, so that they use the regular name if the display name field is empty, I haven\u0027t looked into it. But I\u0027m also using the display name extensively for SCANsat, I can add a check for an empty field, but it\u0027s probably best for Kopernicus to also set it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"strudo76","CreatedById":175831,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-17T10:50:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs it safe to update from -3 to -4 if I don\u0027t have any craft in flight with deployable solar panels?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Thomas P.","CreatedById":113164,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-17T14:54:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Astrofox","CreatedById":135785,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-18T00:16:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerpas is still being a derp:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/2JH2kZrrLGw?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPastebin still in video description.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd yes, I recorded many videos of some systems in my mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are a few more things coming up, so this isn\u0027t the end.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: Here\u0027s even more bugs that I\u0027m struggling with:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/h2VW0aUIJ0c?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMTM-3 doesn\u0027t even look like it\u0027s supposed to. Again, pastebins in desc. of video.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-18T01:59:18Z\u0022 title=\u002206/18/2017 01:59  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 18, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Astrofox\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"panarchist","CreatedById":63336,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-18T07:08:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223093293\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140580\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497592873\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022118622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Errol\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/15/2017 at 11:01 PM, Errol said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBeen out of the loop for a few days. I just upgraded from 1.3.0-2 to 1.3.0-4 and encountered a weird bug. Game loads to menu fine, but when I try to load a save I get stuck partially on loading screen. What I mean is that mod dialogues show up, like the RT settings dialogue on new saves and the KCT build window, but the screen stays black with the planets loading icon in the lower right corner. Also; it is missing the word LOADING when this happens. Reverting to 1.3.0-2 fixes it. I tried 1.3.0-3 as well and got the exact same bug.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m seeing this too, and I am *not* running any Sigma mods. \u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113260-sigma88/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022113260\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113260-sigma88/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Sigma88\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0- specifically, this happens with 1.3.0.1 and 1.3.0.3 - 1.3.0.4, but NOT 1.3.0.2. \u00A0Also, not on every mod I have loaded. \u00A0OPM is fine, and Kepsilon Keridani is also fine, but I see the behavior with Other Worlds (Cercani). \u00A0I\u0027ll see about reinstalling one of the affected versions and posting the log file - there were definitely errors recorded in the log, but I didn\u0027t preserve it before reverting back to the older version. \u00A0Will update when I\u0027ve reproduced it and uploaded logs to Dropbox or somewhere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Errol","CreatedById":118622,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-18T08:18:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/63336-panarchist/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002263336\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/63336-panarchist/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@panarchist\u003C/a\u003E I updated sigma binary, which is one of the recommended mods for OPM, to enable binary systems for duna/ike, and plock/karen as well. This fixed the bug for me. Check to see you have the latest sigma binary, released yesterday I think it was? (so hard to remember, with so many updates)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-18T08:41:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223095442\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140580\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497769712\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002263336\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022panarchist\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, panarchist said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m seeing this too, and I am *not* running any Sigma mods. \u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113260-sigma88/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022113260\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113260-sigma88/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Sigma88\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0- specifically, this happens with 1.3.0.1 and 1.3.0.3 - 1.3.0.4, but NOT 1.3.0.2. \u00A0Also, not on every mod I have loaded. \u00A0OPM is fine, and Kepsilon Keridani is also fine, but I see the behavior with Other Worlds (Cercani). \u00A0I\u0027ll see about reinstalling one of the affected versions and posting the log file - there were definitely errors recorded in the log, but I didn\u0027t preserve it before reverting back to the older version. \u00A0Will update when I\u0027ve reproduced it and uploaded logs to Dropbox or somewhere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPing me once you upload the logs, I\u0027ll take a look as soon as I have some free time\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"panarchist","CreatedById":63336,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-18T14:42:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223095480\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140580\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497773902\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022118622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Errol\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Errol said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/63336-panarchist/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002263336\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/63336-panarchist/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@panarchist\u003C/a\u003E I updated sigma binary, which is one of the recommended mods for OPM, to enable binary systems for duna/ike, and plock/karen as well. This fixed the bug for me. Check to see you have the latest sigma binary, released yesterday I think it was? (so hard to remember, with so many updates)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, I\u0027ll check - though I haven\u0027t installed any optional OPM components. OPM doesn\u0027t have any issues in the stock install, I\u0027ve only seen this issue when Other Worlds and OPM are both installed. If I install only Other Worlds, then it just doesn\u0027t show the extra bodies from that mod, but the save will load.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113260-sigma88/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022113260\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113260-sigma88/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Sigma88\u003C/a\u003E I should be able to reproduce it and get logs up later today - I want to do this on a stripped down version (which I originally tested) since my main game save has 60 mods. \u00A0The behavior reproduces on *just* Kopernicus\u002BOPM\u002BOther Worlds, so I want logs from a clean save on a sparse GameData folder before I ask anyone to chase it down. \u00A0Thanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-18T14:43:10Z\u0022 title=\u002206/18/2017 02:43  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 18, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by panarchist\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bottle Rocketeer 500","CreatedById":178766,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-18T19:34:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113164-thomas-p/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022113164\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113164-thomas-p/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Thomas P.\u003C/a\u003E,\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113260-sigma88/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022113260\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113260-sigma88/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Sigma88\u003C/a\u003E, How can I make planets radiate heat using Kopernicus?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-18T19:45:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223096073\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140580\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497814471\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022178766\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bottle Rocketeer 500\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Bottle Rocketeer 500 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113164-thomas-p/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022113164\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113164-thomas-p/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Thomas P.\u003C/a\u003E,\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113260-sigma88/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022113260\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113260-sigma88/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Sigma88\u003C/a\u003E, How can I make planets radiate heat using Kopernicus?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ndepends on what you mean\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI assume you might find useful \u003Cstrong\u003E\u0022HazardousOcean\u0022\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbasically, you add a node called HazardousOcean inside the Ocean node of the planet, and then define a curve inside that node\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nsomething like this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cpre class=\u0022ipsCode prettyprint lang-html prettyprinted\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003EOcean\n{\n\tHazardousOcean\n\t{\n\t\tkey = 1, 4\n\t\tkey = 2, 5\n\t\tkey = 3, 6\n\t}\n}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nevery key defines a point in the curve, the first number is altitude, and the second number is \u0022additional temperature\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bottle Rocketeer 500","CreatedById":178766,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-18T19:47:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113260-sigma88/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022113260\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/113260-sigma88/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Sigma88\u003C/a\u003E,Can I add the Hazardous Ocean node in the surface node of a planet?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sigma88","CreatedById":113260,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-18T20:00:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223096086\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022140580\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forum